    accessdate = 18 May 2010
  format=PDF The expeditionary force, under the command of Major general United States Major general William Rufus Shafter, landed east of the city and attacked it on 1 July.Hale, Famous Sea fights, from Salamis to Tsu-shima, p. 286. Cervera saw that his situation was desperate and attempted to run the blockade on 3 July 1898, resulting in the battle of Santiago de Cuba. The cruisers USS New Orleans CL-22 New Orleans and  USS Newark C-1 Newark and battleship USS Massachusetts BB-2 Massachusetts had left the day before to coal in Guantanamo Bay.Graham & Schley, Schley and Santiago, pp. 299-300. Also Admiral Sampson's flagship, the cruiser USS New York ACR-2 New York, had sailed east earlier that morning for a meeting with General Shafter,Hale, Famous Sea fights, from Salamis to Tsu-shima, p. 288. leaving Commodore Schley in command. This left the blockade weakened and unbalanced on the day of the battle, as  three modern battleships Indiana, USS Oregon BB-3 Oregon and USS Iowa BB-4 Iowa and armed yacht USS Gloucester 1891 Gloucester guarded the east, while the west was only defended by second-class battleship USS Texas 1892 Texas, cruiser USS Brooklyn CA-3 Brooklyn and armed yacht USS Vixen PY-4 Vixen.Graham & Schley, Schley and Santiago, pp. 303-304.
Indianaoccupying the extreme eastern position of the blockadefired at the cruisers Spanish cruiser Infanta Maria Teresa Infanta Maria Teresa and Spanish cruiser Almirante Oquendo Almirante Oquendo as they left the harbor,Graham & Schley, Schley and Santiago, p. 316.Cite news
